display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi \in  S_{n}]]></fr:tex> be a permutation. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[N]]></fr:tex> be the number of inversion pairs of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi ]]></fr:tex>. Then the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Sign</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi ]]></fr:tex> is the integer <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {sgn}}\nolimits (\pi )]]></fr:tex> equal to
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {sgn}}\nolimits (\pi )=(-1)^{N}]]></fr:tex>
We call <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\pi ]]></fr:tex> an <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Even Permutation</html:dfn> if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {sgn}}\nolimits (\pi )=+1]]></fr:tex> and an <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Odd Permutation</html:dfn> if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {sgn}}\nolimits (\pi )=-1]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
