title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Definition 8.2.1</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="vectsp-000O.xml"
addr="vectsp-000O"
title="Finite-Dimensional Vector Space">Finite-Dimensional Vector Space</fr:link> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B=(e_{1},…,e_{n})]]></fr:tex> be an ordered basis of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L\colon  V\to  V]]></fr:tex> be a linear operator of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>. Suppose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M(L)=(a_{ij})]]></fr:tex> is the matrix of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> with respect to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>. Then we define the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Determinant</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> to be
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\det (L)=\sum _{\pi \in  S_{n}}\mathop {\textrm {sgn}}\nolimits (\pi )a_{1,\pi (1)}a_{2,\pi (2)}(…)a_{n,\pi (n)}]]></fr:tex>
where the sum is taken over all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n!]]></fr:tex> permutations.</fr:p><fr:p>Compare this to the <fr:link
type="local"
href="matrix-001J.xml"
addr="matrix-001J"
title="Determinant">notion</fr:link> in elementary linear algebra.</fr:p><fr:p>To prove this is well-defined, we should prove this is independent of choice of basis. If we changed basis to a basis <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[[L]_{C}=M^{B}_{C}[L]_{B}M^{C}_{B}]]></fr:tex> and the determinant of both  sides are the same since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M^{B}_{C}=(M^{C}_{B})^{-1}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:link
type="local"
href="matrix-001Z.xml"
addr="matrix-001Z"
title="Determinant of inverse is inverse of determinant">Determinant of inverse is inverse of determinant</fr:link>, and <fr:link
type="local"
href="matrix-001V.xml"
addr="matrix-001V"
title="Determinant of product is product of determinants">Determinant of product is product of determinants</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
